modules.description: This module defines a duration type and provides conversions to and from nanoseconds. It supports customizable formatting through a format module reference, allowing durations to be displayed in different representations. It is used to measure and display time intervals in performance monitoring contexts.

This module controls runtime recording of module startup times, exposing a boolean flag to enable recording and an environment variable to trigger it. It includes a `Duration` module for representing and formatting time intervals in nanoseconds, with support for custom display formats. It is used to measure and log performance metrics during module initialization.
